snippet.textDisplay: I have a dear friend who is 79 years old and has a compromised immune system.  He wears a N95 mask whenever he goes out to the grocery store or anywhere there are crowds.  He has also been vaccinated and boosted.  However, he eats out in restaurants fairly often.  He tested positive for Covid yesterday and is now on Paxlovid and quarantining but is still very sick.  He is sorry he believed that the virus was gone & it was OK to eat out.  I hope he gets past this and recovers!
